    <!-- TEXT SECTION -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="sections/new/text-section/text-section.css" />
    <section class="text-section">
        <div class="container">
            <article>
                <p>If you've seen board-certified dermatologists talking about Micro-Infusion, you're not imagining it.</p>
                <p>This treatment is quickly becoming the go-to alternative to expensive creams because it delivers active ingredients past the skin barrier - without the waste, waiting, or watching your serums evaporate on the surface.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- TEXT SECTION END -->

    <!-- BASE SECTION -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="sections/new/base-section/base-section.css" />
    <section class="base-section base-section--reverse">
        <div class="container">
            <article>
                <strong>Reason #1</strong>
                <h2>Your Creams Stop at the Surface</h2>
                <div class="wistia-embed-video">
                    <div class="wistia_responsive_padding">
                        <div class="wistia_responsive_wrapper">
                            <div class="wistia_embed wistia_async_a1pykz2tp0 seo=false videoFoam=true"></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <p>Here's the truth most skincare brands won't tell you: expensive creams and serums can only sit on top of your skin.</p>
                    <p>Your skin's natural barrier blocks most active ingredients from reaching the deeper layers where they actually work.</p>
                    <p>Qure's Micro-Infusion System changes the game. Using 24K gold-plated microneedles (thinner than a strand of hair), it creates tiny surface channels that allow powerful serums to penetrate beyond your skin's barrier—delivering ingredients exactly where they're needed for visible results.</p>
                    <div class="c-note">
                        <p>"Traditional creams and serums struggle to penetrate the skin barrier effectively. Micro-infusion technology creates precise channels that allow active ingredients to reach the deeper layers where they can actually transform your skin."</p>
                        <p><strong>- Dr. Shah, Board Certified Dermatologist</strong></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
    <script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
            loadScriptOnce('wistia-script', 'https://fast.wistia.com/assets/external/E-v1.js');
        });
    </script>
    <!-- BASE SECTION END -->

    <!-- BASE SECTION -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="sections/new/base-section/base-section.css" />
    <section class="base-section base-section--reverse">
        <div class="container">
            <article>
                <strong>Reason #2</strong>
                <h2>Dermatologists Say It's More Effective</h2>
