                <div>
                    <p>You've probably spent hundreds on luxury creams that promised miracles but delivered disappointment.</p>
                    <p>Here's what leading dermatologists recommend instead: micro-infusion technology.</p>
                    <p>This medical-grade approach combines two proven actions in one treatment—mechanical stimulation that helps visibly smooth fine lines, plus direct serum delivery through microscopic channels for maximum absorption.</p>
                    <p>The result? Professional-level efficacy without the clinic price tag or appointment hassle.</p>
                    <div class="c-note">
                        <p>"Micro-infusion combines the benefits of targeted serum delivery with mechanical stimulation. It's a dual-action approach that outperforms topical application alone - giving you professional results at home."</p>
                        <p><strong>- Dr. Shah, Board Certified Dermatologist</strong></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- BASE SECTION END -->

    <!-- BASE SECTION -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="sections/new/base-section/base-section.css" />
    <section class="base-section base-section--reverse">
        <div class="container">
            <article>
                <strong>Reason #3</strong>
                <h2>See Results Overnight (Not in 8-12 Weeks)</h2>
                <picture>
                    <img src="sections/new/base-section/images/microinfusion-listicle-2.webp" alt="See Results Overnight (Not in 8-12 Weeks)" />
                </picture>
                <div>
                    <p>Remember reading "results in 8-12 weeks" on your last cream purchase?</p>
                    <p>That's the skincare industry's way of managing expectations—because surface-level products take months to show minimal change.</p>
                    <p>Qure users report visible differences after just one treatment. That glass-skin glow, refreshed texture, and dewy radiance you've been chasing? It's achievable in a single 5-minute session.</p>
                    <p>Perfect for transforming dull, tired-looking skin before events or any time you want to feel camera-ready.</p>
                    <div class="c-note">
                        <p>"When active ingredients penetrate beyond the surface barrier, you see results dramatically faster. What takes creams 8-12 weeks can happen in days with proper delivery technology."</p>
                        <p><strong>- Dr. Shah, Board Certified Dermatologist</strong></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- BASE SECTION END -->

    <!-- BASE SECTION -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="sections/new/base-section/base-section.css" />
    <section class="base-section base-section--reverse">
        <div class="container">
            <article>
                <strong>Reason #4</strong>
                <h2>Stop Wasting Money on Products That Can't Penetrate</h2>
                <picture>
                    <img src="sections/new/base-section/images/microinfusion-listicle-3.webp" alt="Stop Wasting Money on Products That Can't Penetrate" />
                </picture>
                <div>
                    <p>Let's do the math on your current routine:<br />
                        Vitamin C serum ($65), retinol cream ($80), dark spot treatment ($75), hyaluronic acid ($55).</p>
                    <p>That's $275+ every 2-3 months on products that mostly evaporate or rub off on your pillowcase.</p>
                    <p>Qure's targeted serum delivery ensures you're not wasting a single drop. The micro-infusion channels allow significantly more absorption compared to topical application alone.</p>
                    <p>You use less product and get exponentially better results.</p>
                    <div class="c-note">
                        <p>"Most patients don't realize that up to 90% of their expensive serums never penetrate the skin. Micro-infusion technology maximizes absorption, making every drop count."</p>
                        <p><strong>- Dr. Shah, Board Certified Dermatologist</strong></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- BASE SECTION END -->

    <!-- BASE SECTION -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="sections/new/base-section/base-section.css" />
    <section class="base-section base-section--reverse">
        <div class="container">
            <article>
                <strong>Reason #5</strong>
                <h2>Virtually Painless & Zero Downtime</h2>
                <picture>
                    <img src="sections/new/base-section/images/microinfusion-listicle-4.webp" alt="Virtually Painless & Zero Downtime" />
                </picture>
                <div>
                    <p>Here's what you won't experience with Qure:<br />
                        The burning sensation of harsh chemical peels, the irritation of overloaded cream formulas, or the redness and peeling from aggressive treatments.</p>
                    <p>The EO-sterilized 24K gold needles are so fine (0.5mm) that most users describe the sensation as a gentle pressing—not piercing.</p>
                    <p>Minimal redness typically fades by morning. You can literally do your treatment before bed and wake up glowing the next day.</p>
                    <div class="c-note">
                        <p>"The 24K gold-plated needles at 0.5mm are designed for comfort. Most patients report minimal discomfort and can resume their normal routine immediately, unlike aggressive treatments that require days of recovery."</p>
                        <p><strong>- Dr. Shah, Board Certified Dermatologist</strong></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>
    <!-- BASE SECTION END -->

